Raise your hand
if you get the answer

499
00:39:57,143 --> 00:40:00,476
Let's see who comes first,
who comes last

500
00:40:01,351 --> 00:40:04,560
Your time starts... now

501
00:40:34,226 --> 00:40:35,226
Time up

502
00:40:37,685 --> 00:40:38,685
Time up, sir

503
00:40:40,560 --> 00:40:42,893
No one got the answer?

504
00:40:45,435 --> 00:40:48,768
Now rewind your life by a minute

505
00:40:50,018 --> 00:40:52,810
When I asked this question,
were you excited? Curious?

506
00:40:53,018 --> 00:40:55,726
Thrilled that you'd learn
something new?

507
00:40:56,560 --> 00:40:58,935
Anyone?... Sir?

508
00:41:01,893 --> 00:41:04,685
No. You all got into a frantic race

509
00:41:06,768 --> 00:41:08,888
What's the use of such methods,
even if you come first

510
00:41:11,143 --> 00:41:14,476
Will your knowledge increase?
No, just the pressure

511
00:41:15,435 --> 00:41:16,995
This is a college,
not a pressure cooker

512
00:41:19,185 --> 00:41:22,685
Even a circus lion learns to sit
on a chair in fear of the whip

513
00:41:23,810 --> 00:41:27,392
But you call such a lion
'well trained', not 'well educated'

514
00:41:27,393 --> 00:41:28,393
Hello!

515
00:41:28,851 --> 00:41:33,393
This is not a philosophy class.
Just explain those two words

516
00:41:33,810 --> 00:41:35,476
Sir, these words don't exist

517
00:41:36,685 --> 00:41:39,976
These are my friends' names.
Farhan and Raju

518
00:41:52,560 --> 00:41:53,560
Quiet!

519
00:41:54,976 --> 00:41:57,768
Nonsense! Is this how
you'll teach Engineering?

520
00:41:58,268 --> 00:42:00,143
Sir, I wasn't teaching
you Engineering

521
00:42:00,768 --> 00:42:02,226
You're an expert at that

522
00:42:03,101 --> 00:42:06,310
I was teaching you... how to teach

523
00:42:09,185 --> 00:42:11,060
And I'm sure one day you'll learn

524
00:42:12,101 --> 00:42:15,060
because unlike you, I never
abandon my weak students

525
00:42:15,601 --> 00:42:16,601
Bye, sir

526
00:42:18,685 --> 00:42:19,726
Quiet!

527
00:42:22,310 --> 00:42:23,393
Quiet, I said

528
00:42:26,893 --> 00:42:30,226
<i>I regret to inform you
that your son...</i>

529
00:42:30,393 --> 00:42:31,476
<i>Farhan... Raju...</i>

530
00:42:31,768 --> 00:42:32,848
<i>has fallen into bad company</i>

531
00:42:33,185 --> 00:42:36,310
<i>Without urgent corrective steps,
his future will be ruined</i>

532
00:42:37,435 --> 00:42:40,685
<i>Virus's letters dropped on
our homes like atom bombs</i>

533
00:42:41,018 --> 00:42:43,559
<i>Hiroshima and Nagasaki
plunged into gloom</i>

534
00:42:43,560 --> 00:42:46,601
<i>Our parents invited us -
for a dressing down</i>

535
00:42:47,685 --> 00:42:49,810
Come in

536
00:42:52,393 --> 00:42:53,393
See that?

537
00:42:54,726 --> 00:42:57,268
We could afford
just one air-conditioner

538
00:42:59,060 --> 00:43:02,685
We put it in Farhan's room,
so he could study in comfort

539
00:43:04,185 --> 00:43:08,101
I didn't buy a car.
I manage with a scooter

540
00:43:09,018 --> 00:43:10,851
We put all our money
into Farhan's education

541
00:43:12,393 --> 00:43:16,476
We sacrificed our comforts
for Farhan's future. Understand?

542
00:43:25,143 --> 00:43:26,476
You took these pictures, Farhan?

543
00:43:28,435 --> 00:43:30,393
He had that useless
obsession for a while

544
00:43:31,393 --> 00:43:33,142
Went around taking
pictures of animals

545
00:43:33,143 --> 00:43:35,893
Wanted to be a
wildlife photographer

546
00:43:37,143 --> 00:43:39,518
Son, what was your
score that year?

547
00:43:40,518 --> 00:43:41,685
91%

548
00:43:42,060 --> 00:43:46,685
Hear that? Straight drop
from 94% to 91%

549
00:43:49,851 --> 00:43:51,268
You find it funny?

550
00:43:51,976 --> 00:43:56,018
No sir, sorry. I'm just
amazed at the photos

551
00:43:56,226 --> 00:43:58,810
Why make him an engineer...
Why not a wildlife photographer?

552
00:43:59,018 --> 00:44:00,143
Enough!

553
00:44:01,435 --> 00:44:06,685
I humbly request you -
Don't ruin my son's future

554
00:44:08,226 --> 00:44:10,560
Food's on the table, boys. C'mon

555
00:44:15,518 --> 00:44:17,768
If you ever visit again,
do eat with us

556
00:44:20,726 --> 00:44:22,143
<i>Dad denied us a meal...</i>

557
00:44:22,768 --> 00:44:24,393
<i>So, to fill our bellies with food...</i>

558
00:44:24,810 --> 00:44:28,060
<i>and ears with more reprimands,
we reached Raju's house</i>

559
00:44:30,060 --> 00:44:34,101
<i>Raju's house was straight
out of a 50's black and white film</i>

560
00:44:34,893 --> 00:44:35,893
<i>A small, dingy room...</i>

561
00:44:36,060 --> 00:44:37,518
<i>a paralyzed father...</i>

562
00:44:38,351 --> 00:44:39,518
<i>a coughing mother...</i>

563
00:44:39,935 --> 00:44:41,393
<i>and an unwed sister</i>

564
00:44:42,560 --> 00:44:43,893
<i>A sofa sprouting springs...</i>

565
00:44:44,393 --> 00:44:46,643
<i>a 24 hour water supply -
from the leaking roof</i>

566
00:44:47,351 --> 00:44:50,935
<i>Mother was a retired school
teacher and a tireless complainer</i>

567
00:44:51,643 --> 00:44:53,768
<i>Father was once a postmaster</i>

568
00:44:54,310 --> 00:44:56,685
<i>Paralysis shut down
his body partly...</i>

569
00:44:57,185 --> 00:44:59,560
<i>his salary completely.
And the sister...</i>

570
00:44:59,768 --> 00:45:03,351
Kammo's turned 28.
They demand a car in dowry

571
00:45:04,018 --> 00:45:06,601
If you don't study and earn,
how will she marry?

572
00:45:07,143 --> 00:45:08,143
Some okra?

573
00:45:09,060 --> 00:45:12,893
Okra is now 12Rs per kilo,
cauliflower is 10Rs.

574
00:45:13,268 --> 00:45:14,643
It's daylight robbery!

575
00:45:15,060 --> 00:45:19,018
What will we eat if we get
warnings from your college?

576
00:45:19,310 --> 00:45:20,310
Mom!

577
00:45:21,810 --> 00:45:22,810
Cottage cheese?

578
00:45:23,226 --> 00:45:26,726
Cottage cheese should be sold
at the jewelers, in velvet pouches

579
00:45:27,060 --> 00:45:28,810
Cottage cheese? No, no, it's OK

580
00:45:29,518 --> 00:45:31,018
Mom, please

581
00:45:31,935 --> 00:45:33,685
Alright, I'll shut up

582
00:45:35,393 --> 00:45:39,851
Earn for the family,
slave like a maid

583
00:45:40,101 --> 00:45:42,351
and then take the vow of silence

584
00:45:43,351 --> 00:45:47,851
If not with my son, with whom
do I share my woes - his friends?

585
00:45:51,810 --> 00:45:52,851
Hey Raju

586
00:45:56,435 --> 00:45:57,435
<i>We were in a huge dilemma</i>

587
00:45:58,101 --> 00:46:01,185
<i>Do we comfort our friend
or console his mom?</i>

588
00:46:02,435 --> 00:46:05,351
<i>Screw it, we thought, let's
focus on the cottage cheese</i>

589
00:46:17,310 --> 00:46:20,101
Even his eczema cream
costs 55Rs now

590
00:46:24,893 --> 00:46:26,185
Another roti?

591
00:46:26,560 --> 00:46:29,476
No, thank you. We're through

592
00:46:37,310 --> 00:46:39,851
Okra for 12Rs.
Cauliflower for 10Rs.

593
00:46:42,935 --> 00:46:44,726
At least you were offered a meal

594
00:46:45,601 --> 00:46:48,435
Unlike your sadistic dad...
'Hitler' Qureshi!

595
00:46:48,601 --> 00:46:51,268
And your mom is Mother Teresa...
Feeding us 'eczema roti'!

596
00:46:51,560 --> 00:46:55,101
Don't poke fun at my mom!
Enough, you guys

597
00:46:55,435 --> 00:46:56,810
I'm famished. Let's eat out

598
00:46:56,976 --> 00:46:59,310
It's month end. Who'll pay?
His Mother Teresa?

599
00:47:00,393 --> 00:47:04,935
To eat out, you don't need money.
Just a uniform. Look...

600
00:47:07,768 --> 00:47:09,393
C'mon - Come

601
00:47:11,018 --> 00:47:13,350
Good evening, good evening

602
00:47:13,351 --> 00:47:14,351
Oh, Uncle

603
00:47:19,518 --> 00:47:22,726
Three large vodkas.
Half soda, half water

604
00:47:22,976 --> 00:47:24,185
If we're caught, we're dead

605
00:47:24,393 --> 00:47:27,017
What's for starters?
Get double portions

606
00:47:27,018 --> 00:47:30,018
Leave this here and start
some peppy music

607
00:47:30,810 --> 00:47:32,435
Pia, what the hell!

608
00:47:32,851 --> 00:47:35,518
Why're you wearing
this ancient piece of junk?

609
00:47:36,768 --> 00:47:40,310
What'll people say - My fiancée...

610
00:47:40,768 --> 00:47:43,310
a doctor in the making,
wearing a cheap, 200Rs watch!

611
00:47:44,268 --> 00:47:45,726
Please take it off. Thank you

612
00:47:46,310 --> 00:47:47,310
Hi handsome

613
00:47:47,476 --> 00:47:50,392
Hey Aunty. You're looking good

614
00:47:50,393 --> 00:47:52,935
Don't miss my set, darling
Rubies?

615
00:47:53,143 --> 00:47:55,850
From Mandalay - Mandalay... Wow!

616
00:47:55,851 --> 00:47:58,518
Hey, let's go meet David
Of course

617
00:48:01,893 --> 00:48:02,893
Excuse me

618
00:48:04,976 --> 00:48:06,101
Yes?

619
00:48:06,435 --> 00:48:07,476
Flowers

620
00:48:09,018 --> 00:48:12,185
- May I take the glass?
- Why?

621
00:48:12,518 --> 00:48:14,768
So you don't break it on my head

622
00:48:15,601 --> 00:48:16,810
Why would I do that?

623
00:48:17,268 --> 00:48:19,351
For the free advice I'll now impart

624
00:48:20,560 --> 00:48:21,560
What?

625
00:48:21,768 --> 00:48:23,310
Don't marry that ass

626
00:48:24,435 --> 00:48:25,435
Excuse me?

627
00:48:25,560 --> 00:48:27,226
He's not a human,
he's a price tag

628
00:48:27,685 --> 00:48:30,643
He'll turn your life into a
nightmare of brands and prices

629
00:48:31,310 --> 00:48:33,851
He'll ruin your life.
Your future will be finished

630
00:48:34,185 --> 00:48:35,185
Want a demonstration?

631
00:48:37,226 --> 00:48:38,810
Shall I find out
the price of his shoes?

632
00:48:40,393 --> 00:48:42,268
I won't ask.
He'll announce it himself

633
00:48:54,351 --> 00:49:00,268
What the hell...
Mint sauce on my $300 shoes!

634
00:49:00,435 --> 00:49:03,601
Run for your life!
It's free advice. Take it or leave it

635
00:49:04,185 --> 00:49:06,851
Genuine Italian leather -
hand-stitched!

636
00:49:11,476 --> 00:49:14,143
Dad, are they your guests?

637
00:49:17,518 --> 00:49:20,768
My students.
What're they doing here?

638
00:49:24,768 --> 00:49:25,935
Hold on, Dad

639
00:49:27,518 --> 00:49:29,726
These beans smell great

640
00:49:29,893 --> 00:49:32,185
No room for roti Just pile it on

641
00:49:34,185 --> 00:49:35,518
Hi - Hey

642
00:49:37,101 --> 00:49:40,060
That was an eye-opener.
Thank you so much

643
00:49:41,601 --> 00:49:43,851
It was my moral responsibility

644
00:49:44,685 --> 00:49:46,085
Can I ask you for little more help?

645
00:49:47,185 --> 00:49:49,768
Dad won't let me break off
this engagement

646
00:49:50,768 --> 00:49:54,726
You explain so well.
Can you give him a demo too?

647
00:49:55,060 --> 00:49:57,643
Certainly. Raju, the mint sauce

648
00:49:58,226 --> 00:49:59,643
You're really sweet

649
00:50:00,893 --> 00:50:03,935
Where is your daddy?
Right behind you

650
00:50:08,601 --> 00:50:10,893
Aal izz well

651
00:50:11,726 --> 00:50:16,851
Run for your life!
It's free advice. Take it or leave it

652
00:50:17,185 --> 00:50:18,685
What're you doing here?

653
00:50:19,351 --> 00:50:22,435
We'll hand these gifts
to the couple

654
00:50:23,518 --> 00:50:25,768
I'll do that for you.
It's my sister's wedding

655
00:50:26,226 --> 00:50:27,351
Sister?

656
00:50:30,226 --> 00:50:32,601
Sir, what's the sum total
of your daughters?

657
00:50:34,226 --> 00:50:35,226
Empty. No gift cheques

658
00:50:35,435 --> 00:50:37,600
Forgot the cheques, Raju
...Farhan?

659
00:50:37,601 --> 00:50:41,726
We didn't invite you,
you must be from the groom's side

660
00:50:42,268 --> 00:50:46,185
No sir, we're here as the
emissaries of science

661
00:50:46,351 --> 00:50:48,518
How? Can you explain?

662
00:50:48,810 --> 00:50:52,435
Dad, he explains superbly.
I'm sure he'll give us a demo

663
00:50:52,768 --> 00:50:53,768
Won't you?

664
00:50:54,560 --> 00:50:58,101
Well, Delhi has plenty of
power cuts that...

665
00:50:58,393 --> 00:51:00,685
disrupt wedding celebrations

666
00:51:01,060 --> 00:51:03,143
So I thought of making
an inverter that...

667
00:51:03,310 --> 00:51:05,685
draws power from guests' cars

668
00:51:05,935 --> 00:51:07,268
I see

669
00:51:07,518 --> 00:51:08,976
Wow

670
00:51:09,393 --> 00:51:10,768
So where's the inverter?

671
00:51:11,601 --> 00:51:13,185
Sir, the design is ready

672
00:51:16,310 --> 00:51:17,560
Where's the design, Farhan?

673
00:51:18,018 --> 00:51:21,018
I gave you the design
I gave it to Raju

674
00:51:21,476 --> 00:51:22,476
Raju, design?

675
00:51:25,518 --> 00:51:29,226
Never mind the design.
I'll make the inverter and show you

676
00:51:29,601 --> 00:51:33,226
You can only invent stories,
not an inverter

677
00:51:33,560 --> 00:51:36,601
I'll make one, I promise

678
00:51:36,976 --> 00:51:40,435
And I'll name it after you.
After all, it was invented...

679
00:51:40,893 --> 00:51:44,351
at your daughter's wedding.
So it'll be an honor...

680
00:51:44,518 --> 00:51:50,518
Farhan, Raju. I'll see you
in my office tomorrow

681
00:51:56,435 --> 00:51:59,893
Sir, what was the cost per plate?
We'll reimburse you

682
00:52:00,268 --> 00:52:01,893
...in installments

683
00:52:04,393 --> 00:52:07,601
We'll never crash a wedding again
Not even my own

684
00:52:07,768 --> 00:52:09,976
In fact, I won't even marry.
Nor will he

685
00:52:10,685 --> 00:52:12,685
Uh... right. No marriage

686
00:52:14,226 --> 00:52:16,560
Your parents shouldn't have
married either

687
00:52:18,268 --> 00:52:20,768
The world would have
to feed two less idiots

688
00:52:23,310 --> 00:52:24,310
Sit!

689
00:52:35,351 --> 00:52:36,351
Pay attention

690
00:52:47,310 --> 00:52:52,226
This is Ranchhoddas's father's
monthly income

691
00:52:53,601 --> 00:52:59,893
Couple of zeroes less,
and it's still a sizable income

692
00:53:02,476 --> 00:53:08,768
But erase another zero,
and I would worry a little

693
00:53:10,060 --> 00:53:13,393
Isn't that your fathers income,
Farhan?

694
00:53:14,310 --> 00:53:15,976
Yes, sir

695
00:53:17,393 --> 00:53:19,393
Now take away another zero...

696
00:53:22,476 --> 00:53:26,226
and that's your family income,
Raju Rastogi

697
00:53:27,435 --> 00:53:28,768
Big reason to worry

698
00:53:33,518 --> 00:53:40,643
Take my advice and shift into
Chatur Ramalingam's room

699
00:53:41,101 --> 00:53:45,310
Exams are here. Stay with
Rancho and you're sure to fail

700
00:54:07,268 --> 00:54:09,643
- Want a shave?
- No, sir

701
00:54:09,851 --> 00:54:10,851
Then get lost!

702
00:54:21,976 --> 00:54:27,518
Raju, don't worry. This is Virus's
move to split us. Divide and rule

703
00:54:27,685 --> 00:54:28,726
I have to worry

704
00:54:29,185 --> 00:54:32,643
He grades us, and I need
good grades for a good job

705
00:54:33,601 --> 00:54:36,601
Unlike you, I don't have a
rich dad I can live off

706
00:54:36,768 --> 00:54:38,601
Shut up, Raju

707
00:54:38,893 --> 00:54:41,518
Must we follow all his hogwash?
'Aal izz well'

708
00:54:41,935 --> 00:54:43,351
I won't be his flunky... like you

709
00:54:44,351 --> 00:54:46,601
You're crossing the line
No, I'm drawing one

710
00:54:47,143 --> 00:54:48,810
I have a family to support

711
00:54:51,060 --> 00:54:53,268
Dad's medicines
swallow up mom's pension

712
00:54:55,268 --> 00:54:59,601
My sis can't marry because
they want a car in dowry

713
00:55:02,560 --> 00:55:06,768
Mom hasn't bought a
single saree in five years

714
00:55:09,643 --> 00:55:12,810
Now don't get your mom's
wardrobe into the debate

715
00:55:13,976 --> 00:55:16,016
By the way, how many sarees
per annum is reasonable?

716
00:55:17,060 --> 00:55:18,268
Hey... no wisecracks about mom

717
00:55:19,060 --> 00:55:23,268
We'll study with all our heart,
but not just for grades

718
00:55:23,976 --> 00:55:28,268
To quote a Wise One - Study
to be accomplished, not affluent

719
00:55:29,060 --> 00:55:34,560
Follow excellence. And success
will chase you, pants down!

720
00:55:35,810 --> 00:55:38,393
Which Wise One says this?
His Holiness Guru Ranchhoddas?

721
00:55:40,476 --> 00:55:41,476
Go rot in the bogs!

722
00:55:43,101 --> 00:55:46,060
Raju, don't stress. We'll top
our class. Nothing is impossible

723
00:55:46,393 --> 00:55:47,518
Oh yeah?

724
00:55:51,226 --> 00:55:53,310
Shove this back into the tube

725
00:55:56,393 --> 00:55:57,976
<i>Raju got onto another train</i>

726
00:55:58,560 --> 00:56:03,685
<i>His travails with Chatur began.
Yes, I mean travails, not travels</i>

727
00:56:08,143 --> 00:56:10,018
<i>Chatur was called 'Silencer'</i>

728
00:56:10,393 --> 00:56:14,060
<i>To sharpen his memory,
he popped pills from a local quack</i>

729
00:56:14,518 --> 00:56:16,435
<i>And then let off silent...
but lethal farts</i>

730
00:56:19,185 --> 00:56:22,351
I didn't do it... Raju?

731
00:56:22,560 --> 00:56:25,185
<i>He always blamed others
for the output</i>

732
00:56:25,976 --> 00:56:28,810
<i>Silencer crammed 18 hours a day</i>

733
00:56:29,101 --> 00:56:32,185
<i>On exam eve,
he would distract others</i>

734
00:56:36,185 --> 00:56:39,226
<i>His belief - There are only
two ways of topping</i>

735
00:56:39,601 --> 00:56:42,851
<i>Elevate your own grades or
shrink your opponents' grades</i>

736
00:56:47,185 --> 00:56:51,018
<i>Rancho decided to subdue
Silencer and rescue Raju...</i>

737
00:56:51,518 --> 00:56:52,768
<i>with one master plan</i>

738
00:56:54,851 --> 00:57:02,851
Our Director has unceasingly
served... 'Served' means...

739
00:57:02,935 --> 00:57:06,935
Damn the meaning,
I'll memorize it

740
00:57:08,393 --> 00:57:11,976
<i>Chatur was the introductory speaker
at the Teachers' Day function</i>

741
00:57:12,351 --> 00:57:16,226
<i>To impress Virus, he got his
speech written by the librarian...</i>

742
00:57:16,476 --> 00:57:17,768
<i>in highbrow Hindi</i>

743
