01:54:09,851 --> 01:54:13,018
<i>♪ In this journey of few strides</i>

1482
01:54:13,268 --> 01:54:16,226
<i>♪ On the path called life</i>

1483
01:54:16,435 --> 01:54:22,226
<i>♪ Don't quit...
Just celebrate the ride</i>

1484
01:54:23,060 --> 01:54:26,185
<i>♪ Listen please to those
who love you</i>

1485
01:54:26,351 --> 01:54:29,351
<i>♪ Every dark night is
followed by sunrise</i>

1486
01:54:29,726 --> 01:54:34,935
<i>♪ Don't shut out those
who love you</i>

1487
01:54:35,185 --> 01:54:41,643
<i>♪ We won't let go of you</i>

1488
01:54:41,810 --> 01:54:48,101
<i>♪ We're not done yet... no way</i>

1489
01:54:48,351 --> 01:54:54,726
<i>♪ We won't let go of you</i>

1490
01:54:54,893 --> 01:55:02,435
<i>♪ We're not done yet... no way</i>

1491
01:55:05,810 --> 01:55:09,643
Look, mom bought a new saree
Brand new

1492
01:55:09,810 --> 01:55:11,393
It cost 2000Rs.

1493
01:55:12,101 --> 01:55:13,310
Wake up now

1494
01:55:14,518 --> 01:55:16,601
She bought not one,
but ten sarees

1495
01:55:17,101 --> 01:55:18,101
Look!

1496
01:55:20,101 --> 01:55:21,267
Hey Raju!

1497
01:55:21,268 --> 01:55:24,268
C'mon tell me... How do I look?

1498
01:55:25,393 --> 01:55:28,435
<i>♪ Remember the letters
mom would write... ♪</i>

1499
01:55:28,601 --> 01:55:31,685
<i>♪ Always blessed you
with eternal life ♪</i>

1500
01:55:31,893 --> 01:55:37,976
<i>♪ Don't die on her... you can't die ♪</i>

1501
01:55:38,393 --> 01:55:41,560
<i>♪ Look at us now, don't turn away ♪</i>

1502
01:55:41,726 --> 01:55:44,810
<i>♪ Smile once to show you care ♪</i>

1503
01:55:45,018 --> 01:55:49,435
<i>♪ Wake up,
don't torment us anymore ♪</i>

1504
01:55:58,351 --> 01:56:01,768
Did you hear about your sis?

1505
01:56:02,726 --> 01:56:05,393
She's getting married

1506
01:56:06,435 --> 01:56:07,726
Without any dowry

1507
01:56:08,435 --> 01:56:13,310
The bridegroom wants
nothing at all

1508
01:56:13,560 --> 01:56:17,018
He just wants Kammo

1509
01:56:17,685 --> 01:56:21,892
You know who the bridegroom is?
Yeah

1510
01:56:21,893 --> 01:56:22,810
Guess!

1511
01:56:22,811 --> 01:56:24,685
You know him very well - Yes

1512
01:56:24,893 --> 01:56:26,518
He loves animals - Huh...?

1513
01:56:27,351 --> 01:56:29,475
He's going to be a
wildlife photographer

1514
01:56:29,476 --> 01:56:31,142
Quiet... Shhhh...

1515
01:56:31,143 --> 01:56:34,268
Didn't get it? It's our Farhan

1516
01:56:35,268 --> 01:56:39,351
Farhan will never take any dowry

1517
01:56:40,018 --> 01:56:44,351
Farhan will marry your sister

1518
01:56:44,810 --> 01:56:48,935
For free! Free! Free!

1519
01:56:50,018 --> 01:56:52,101
Raju!

1520
01:56:59,101 --> 01:57:02,851
One kilo okra, 500 grams cheese
for 'free' would've woken him

1521
01:57:03,268 --> 01:57:04,976
Why sacrifice me...!

1522
01:57:05,268 --> 01:57:07,226
Well done, buddy

1523
01:57:08,060 --> 01:57:11,560
So it's all fixed -
Farhan will marry your sister

1524
01:57:12,685 --> 01:57:13,685
Rancho

1525
01:57:16,310 --> 01:57:19,435
Rascals... Stop fibbing

1526
01:57:22,060 --> 01:57:23,060
Lucky escape!

1527
01:57:23,268 --> 01:57:29,643
<i>♪ We won't let go of you ♪</i>

1528
01:57:29,810 --> 01:57:36,226
<i>♪ We're not done yet... no way ♪</i>

1529
01:57:36,435 --> 01:57:42,768
<i>♪ We won't let go of you ♪</i>

1530
01:57:42,976 --> 01:57:49,017
<i>♪ We're not done yet... no way ♪</i>

1531
01:57:49,018 --> 01:57:55,476
<i>♪ We won't let go of you ♪</i>

1532
01:57:55,643 --> 01:58:03,643
'Okra Rs.12 / kilo'

1533
01:58:06,893 --> 01:58:08,517
You called for a taxi?

1534
01:58:08,518 --> 01:58:10,268
I did - It's waiting

1535
01:58:10,435 --> 01:58:11,893
Thank you. Why?

1536
01:58:12,351 --> 01:58:13,643
I'm going to the job interview

1537
01:58:13,935 --> 01:58:15,143
You coming with me?

1538
01:58:15,560 --> 01:58:20,143
No. I'm going for the interview.
You're going home

1539
01:58:20,310 --> 01:58:21,643
Why would I go home?

1540
01:58:23,185 --> 01:58:26,601
Remember, we promised
this rascal

1541
01:58:29,976 --> 01:58:32,018
Give me your tie

1542
01:58:33,601 --> 01:58:34,601
Why?

1543
01:58:34,685 --> 01:58:38,560
I doubt you'll go for the
interview after reading this

1544
01:58:39,518 --> 01:58:40,518
What's that?

1545
01:58:40,601 --> 01:58:43,435
A letter - For you, from Hungary

1546
01:58:43,810 --> 01:58:46,393
Some photographer
called Andre Istvan

1547
01:58:54,351 --> 01:58:56,101
You posted my letter!

1548
01:58:56,310 --> 01:58:57,976
He loved your pictures

1549
01:58:58,476 --> 01:59:01,101
The guy wants you to assist him...

1550
01:59:01,935 --> 01:59:05,435
in the Brazilian rain forest,
for a year

1551
01:59:05,851 --> 01:59:07,393
Will pay you, too

1552
01:59:23,351 --> 01:59:24,601
Dad will never agree

1553
01:59:27,226 --> 01:59:29,851
Go speak to him...
from your heart

1554
01:59:31,560 --> 01:59:32,685
For once, dump your fears...

1555
01:59:33,393 --> 01:59:39,393
or someday, on your deathbed,
you'll regret it

1556
01:59:39,935 --> 01:59:42,615
You'll remember that the letter was
in your hand, taxi at the gate...

1557
01:59:42,643 --> 01:59:46,393
With just a little courage, you
could've turned your life around

1558
01:59:52,976 --> 01:59:54,893
Do you think he'll like it?

1559
01:59:55,560 --> 01:59:57,851
Why such an expensive gift?

1560
01:59:59,018 --> 02:00:01,435
Our son's getting
his first job today

1561
02:00:02,768 --> 02:00:06,643
Don't be stingy at
such a proud moment

1562
02:00:08,601 --> 02:00:09,601
Farhan?

1563
02:00:14,685 --> 02:00:16,935
Don't you have
the job interview today?

1564
02:00:18,768 --> 02:00:19,768
I didn't go

1565
02:00:22,393 --> 02:00:24,101
I don't want to be
an engineer, Dad

1566
02:00:28,351 --> 02:00:30,268
What happened?
You had an accident?

1567
02:00:33,935 --> 02:00:39,143
See that building?
I jumped from its third floor

1568
02:00:41,976 --> 02:00:42,976
Why?

1569
02:00:43,226 --> 02:00:45,518
Because I was rusticated
from college

1570
02:00:48,476 --> 02:00:49,476
Why?

1571
02:00:49,810 --> 02:00:54,601
Drunk, I urinated
on the Director's door

1572
02:00:56,935 --> 02:01:00,560
That scoundrel Rancho
is messing with your mind!

1573
02:01:00,726 --> 02:01:04,435
I don't enjoy Engineering.
I'd make a terrible engineer

1574
02:01:06,601 --> 02:01:11,185
Rancho has a simple belief -
Make your passion your profession

1575
02:01:11,560 --> 02:01:13,101
Then work will become play

1576
02:01:13,268 --> 02:01:15,143
What'll you earn in that jungle?

1577
02:01:15,810 --> 02:01:19,517
A small stipend, but I'll learn a lot

1578
02:01:19,518 --> 02:01:20,685
Five years from now...

1579
02:01:21,435 --> 02:01:26,267
when you see your friends buying
cars and homes, you'll curse yourself

1580
02:01:26,268 --> 02:01:30,226
Life as an engineer will bring
only frustration. Then I'll curse you

1581
02:01:32,310 --> 02:01:34,060
I'd rather curse myself, Dad

1582
02:01:34,226 --> 02:01:35,393
The world will laugh!

1583
02:01:36,685 --> 02:01:38,643
Label you a loser,
for quitting in the final year

1584
02:01:39,560 --> 02:01:45,226
Mr. Kapoor feels you're fortunate
to be at ICE. What'll he think?

1585
02:01:45,518 --> 02:01:47,643
Mr. Kapoor didn't provide me
with an air-conditioner

1586
02:01:50,476 --> 02:01:52,956
It wasn't Mr. Kapoor who slept
in discomfort while I slept well

1587
02:01:55,101 --> 02:01:58,060
He didn't take me around the zoo
on his shoulders

1588
02:02:00,935 --> 02:02:02,143
You did all that, Dad

1589
02:02:04,643 --> 02:02:10,060
How you feel, matters to me.
Mr. Kapoor makes no difference

1590
02:02:11,268 --> 02:02:13,101
I don't even know his first name

1591
02:02:13,268 --> 02:02:16,143
You think you're the hero
of a melodrama?

1592
02:02:16,351 --> 02:02:19,060
Enough, please... he's upset

1593
02:02:20,351 --> 02:02:22,768
God forbid, if he did
something crazy like Raju...

1594
02:02:23,018 --> 02:02:24,560
Then the discussion is over

1595
02:02:24,893 --> 02:02:28,643
Don't say a word or
His Lordship will jump off the roof

1596
02:02:32,143 --> 02:02:37,101
No, Dad. I'll never attempt suicide.
I promise

1597
02:02:39,643 --> 02:02:46,601
The Rancho you detest
put this picture in my wallet

1598
02:02:48,226 --> 02:02:52,018
Told me to see it if a suicidal thought
crossed my mind

1599
02:02:52,185 --> 02:02:55,517
and imagine what'd happen
to your smiles

1600
02:02:55,518 --> 02:02:57,268
when you see my dead body

1601
02:03:02,601 --> 02:03:06,601
I want to convince you, Dad

1602
02:03:08,101 --> 02:03:10,518
but not with a suicide threat

1603
02:03:14,310 --> 02:03:18,101
Dad, what'll happen
if I become a photographer?

1604
02:03:18,435 --> 02:03:19,643
I'll earn less

1605
02:03:20,601 --> 02:03:22,268
I'll have a smaller house,
a smaller car

1606
02:03:24,351 --> 02:03:25,851
But I'll be happy

1607
02:03:27,560 --> 02:03:28,810
I will be really happy

1608
02:03:30,143 --> 02:03:32,063
Whatever I do for you
will be out of genuine love

1609
02:03:33,726 --> 02:03:35,435
I've always listened to you

1610
02:03:35,851 --> 02:03:38,935
For once,
let me listen to my heart

1611
02:03:41,060 --> 02:03:42,060
Please... Dad

1612
02:03:48,393 --> 02:03:49,393
Dad...

1613
02:03:50,560 --> 02:03:51,768
Please don't go away...

1614
02:03:58,018 --> 02:03:59,185
Return this

1615
02:04:02,726 --> 02:04:05,143
Son, what's the cost
of a professional camera?

1616
02:04:06,435 --> 02:04:08,185
Can the laptop be exchanged for it?

1617
02:04:09,685 --> 02:04:11,518
If you need more money, just ask

1618
02:04:20,351 --> 02:04:22,268
Go live your life, my son

1619
02:04:25,226 --> 02:04:29,476
Your grades are consistently poor.
Reason?

1620
02:04:30,185 --> 02:04:31,185
Fear

1621
02:04:32,143 --> 02:04:33,543
I was a good student
since childhood

1622
02:04:34,310 --> 02:04:36,435
Parents hoped
I'd end their poverty

1623
02:04:38,393 --> 02:04:39,393
That scared me

1624
02:04:40,893 --> 02:04:44,351
Here I saw the mad race.
You don't count if you're not first

1625
02:04:46,101 --> 02:04:47,101
My fear grew

1626
02:04:48,810 --> 02:04:50,226
Fear is not good for grades, sir

1627
02:04:50,893 --> 02:04:53,268
I slipped on more
charms and rings

1628
02:04:54,310 --> 02:04:58,726
Prayed to God for favors.
No... begged for favors

1629
02:05:01,851 --> 02:05:04,935
16 broken bones gave me
two months to think and reflect

1630
02:05:05,518 --> 02:05:06,726
Finally, sense dawned

1631
02:05:08,268 --> 02:05:13,393
Today I didn't beg God for this job,
just thanked him for this life

1632
02:05:15,893 --> 02:05:19,851
If you reject me, no regrets

1633
02:05:20,226 --> 02:05:24,310
I'll still do something
worthwhile with my life

1634
02:05:24,893 --> 02:05:30,060
Such frank behavior
is not good for our firm

1635
02:05:30,685 --> 02:05:35,059
We need someone diplomatic
to handle clients

1636
02:05:35,060 --> 02:05:37,393
You're too straightforward

1637
02:05:39,310 --> 02:05:40,310
But...

1638
02:05:41,310 --> 02:05:47,726
if you assure us
you'll control this attitude

1639
02:05:47,893 --> 02:05:50,851
we may consider you

1640
02:05:54,226 --> 02:05:57,351
It took two broken legs
to get me up on my feet

1641
02:05:59,268 --> 02:06:01,060
Wasn't easy to get this attitude

1642
02:06:01,810 --> 02:06:02,810
Can't change it, sir

1643
02:06:06,351 --> 02:06:11,560
You keep your job...
I'll keep my attitude

1644
02:06:11,726 --> 02:06:13,060
I'm sorry, no offense, sir

1645
02:06:17,476 --> 02:06:18,476
Wait

1646
02:06:20,310 --> 02:06:24,268
I've interviewed countless
candidates for 25 years

1647
02:06:24,726 --> 02:06:27,560
Everyone turns into
a yes-man to get the job

1648
02:06:27,768 --> 02:06:29,101
Where did you spring from, son?

1649
02:06:31,060 --> 02:06:32,060
Sir?

1650
02:06:32,143 --> 02:06:34,726
Shall we discuss the salary?

1651
02:06:42,310 --> 02:06:43,310
Thank you, sir

1652
02:07:15,768 --> 02:07:19,935
Your Majesty, thou art great

1653
02:07:21,893 --> 02:07:23,518
Accept this humble offering

1654
02:08:00,143 --> 02:08:03,560
Govind!

1655
02:08:05,643 --> 02:08:09,101
You had said, 'If he gets a job,
shave it off'

1656
02:08:16,351 --> 02:08:17,351
What have you done?

1657
02:08:20,976 --> 02:08:24,351
I feel naked without
my moustache

1658
02:08:26,685 --> 02:08:28,560
I've lost my dignity

1659
02:08:30,685 --> 02:08:33,101
I won't accept defeat, Rastogi

1660
02:08:34,435 --> 02:08:38,435
The job isn't yours until you
pass your final exam

1661
02:08:39,935 --> 02:08:43,851
And this time,
I will set the question paper

1662
02:08:47,101 --> 02:08:49,643
Dad, that's not fair

1663
02:08:52,018 --> 02:08:55,518
Everything is fair in
Love and War

1664
02:08:56,060 --> 02:08:59,351
And this is World War... III

1665
02:09:00,851 --> 02:09:01,891
Rastogi, you're dead meat!

1666
02:09:06,851 --> 02:09:07,851
Hey

1667
02:09:10,185 --> 02:09:11,185
What're you doing here?

1668
02:09:14,060 --> 02:09:15,060
Be careful

1669
02:09:20,601 --> 02:09:24,435
You've been drinking
Yup, had to down a couple

1670
02:09:25,018 --> 02:09:27,309
A couple too many!

1671
02:09:27,310 --> 02:09:29,185
Needed the guts - For what?

1672
02:09:30,976 --> 02:09:32,476
For stealing this - What's this?

1673
02:09:33,601 --> 02:09:37,726
The duplicate key to
Virus's office

1674
02:09:40,268 --> 02:09:42,560
The question paper's
in a cover with a red seal

1675
02:09:43,268 --> 02:09:47,226
Dad has set it, to fail Raju

1676
02:09:47,560 --> 02:09:48,560
Go get it!

1677
02:09:49,560 --> 02:09:52,101
Are you mad or what -
that's cheating!

1678
02:09:56,601 --> 02:09:59,810
Everything's fair in
Love and War

1679
02:10:01,351 --> 02:10:02,351
Tell me something...

1680
02:10:04,310 --> 02:10:05,476
Do you really feel...

1681
02:10:07,060 --> 02:10:12,560
the noses collide while kissing?

1682
02:10:18,018 --> 02:10:21,726
Wait. Have some dhokla

1683
02:10:24,226 --> 02:10:26,810
You Gujaratis are so cute

1684
02:10:27,768 --> 02:10:31,060
But why does your food
sound so dangerous?

1685
02:10:32,185 --> 02:10:37,393
Dhokla, Fafda, Handwa,
Thepla, Khakhra

1686
02:10:38,560 --> 02:10:40,725
Sound like missiles

1687
02:10:40,726 --> 02:10:41,726
C'mon

1688
02:10:41,810 --> 02:10:44,268
'Today Bush dropped
two Dhoklas on Iraq'

1689
02:10:44,935 --> 02:10:47,768
'400 dead, 200 injured'

1690
02:10:48,143 --> 02:10:49,143
C'mon

1691
02:10:52,518 --> 02:10:53,518
Oh...

1692
02:10:55,018 --> 02:10:59,435
I can deal with Khakhra, Fafda.
But your name...

1693
02:11:00,393 --> 02:11:03,685
'Ranchhoddas Shamaldas
Chanchad' - Yuck

1694
02:11:04,935 --> 02:11:07,476
I won't change my last name
after marriage

1695
02:11:09,351 --> 02:11:12,310
Pia, we can't get married

1696
02:11:15,893 --> 02:11:16,893
Why?

1697
02:11:17,643 --> 02:11:19,060
Is there someone else?

1698
02:11:21,601 --> 02:11:22,601
No

1699
02:11:22,768 --> 02:11:24,476
- Are you gay?
- No

1700
02:11:26,351 --> 02:11:28,226
Then why don't you
propose to me?

1701
02:11:32,810 --> 02:11:34,226
- Are you impotent?
- No

1702
02:11:36,935 --> 02:11:38,726
Then prove it

1703
02:11:39,226 --> 02:11:40,226
Pia, no

1704
02:11:40,435 --> 02:11:41,851
Stop, stop!

1705
02:11:42,060 --> 02:11:44,393
What happened?
We didn't inform Pia

1706
02:11:44,893 --> 02:11:47,017
Stop here,
my bladders are bursting

1707
02:11:47,018 --> 02:11:48,851
Shut up!
Are you in touch with her?

1708
02:11:49,185 --> 02:11:52,310
No... I have her home number
Then call her, I'll stop

1709
02:11:58,810 --> 02:11:59,726
Hello

1710
02:11:59,727 --> 02:12:02,017
No place for urine-expulsion
in this country

1711
02:12:02,018 --> 02:12:05,393
Hello, is Pia there?
No, she's not

1712
02:12:05,810 --> 02:12:07,560
Is she at the hospital?

1713
02:12:07,726 --> 02:12:09,268
Why would she be there?

1714
02:12:09,518 --> 02:12:11,685
She's getting married today
in Manali

1715
02:12:19,726 --> 02:12:20,935
Too late! She's married

1716
02:12:22,393 --> 02:12:25,268
Not yet. It's a six hour drive

1717
02:12:25,643 --> 02:12:27,685
If we rush, we'll reach
before the vows

1718
02:12:28,226 --> 02:12:29,226
What do you say?

1719
02:12:31,060 --> 02:12:33,435
It's a no-brainer. Let's turn back

1720
02:12:33,685 --> 02:12:35,393
No turning back

1721
02:12:35,893 --> 02:12:38,601
Straight to Ladakh.
We'll meet Rancho and return

1722
02:12:38,810 --> 02:12:41,351
I have a Friday meeting with
Phunsukh Wangdu

1723
02:12:41,518 --> 02:12:43,018
Get into the car

1724
02:12:43,310 --> 02:12:46,435
If I miss my meeting,
the Japanese will get him

1725
02:12:46,851 --> 02:12:49,226
They're offering him a
first name in the company

1726
02:12:49,393 --> 02:12:52,351
'Phunsukh and Fujiyashi',
profit sharing...

1727
02:13:25,601 --> 02:13:27,726
Pia weds Suhas!
Thanks for the suit

1728
02:13:30,101 --> 02:13:31,560
Virus will have a heart attack

1729
02:13:32,685 --> 02:13:35,351
At every daughter's wedding,
we're there to rock the party

1730
02:13:36,810 --> 02:13:40,185
Listen, I'll update Pia,
you peel off the price tag

1731
02:13:57,018 --> 02:13:59,226
Farhan - We found Rancho

1732
02:14:07,393 --> 02:14:08,976
- For Room 107?
- Yes, sir

1733
02:14:09,726 --> 02:14:12,518
- You've taken ages.
